Kentriodontidae is an extinct family of odontocet whales related to modern dolphins. The Family lived from the Oligocene to the Pliocene before going extinct.

Taxonomy
The kentriodontids are grouped in three subfamilies with two genera considered incertae sedis, or of uncertain placement in the family.
Family Kentriodontidae Subfamily Kentriodontinae Belonodelphis  Delphinodon  Incacetus  Kentriodon (syn. Grypolithax)  Macrokentriodon  Microphocaena  Rudicetus  Tagicetus   Subfamily Lophocetinae Hadrodelphis  Liolithax  Lophocetus   Subfamily Pithanodelphininae Atocetus  Leptodelphis  Pithanodelphis  Sophianacetus (syn. Mediocris)   Subfamily incertae sedis Sarmatodelphis  Kampholophos   

